    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 European War 1939/1074: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-01">September 1,
                            1943</date>.<lb/>[Received September 1—11:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1997. Department’s 1132, 13th [<hi rend="italic">30th</hi>].<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d479fn16">See footnote 5, <ref target="#pg_461">p. 461</ref>.</note>
                    Foreign Office made public last evening text of reply to British note regarding
                    war criminal refugees. Communiqué stated similar reply made to this Embassy but
                    we have not yet received it.<note n="17" xml:id="d479fn17">Copy of reply
                        transmitted to the Department by the Chargé in Argentina in his despatch No.
                        11722, September 1.</note> Note states in substance that Argentine
                    Government distinguishes between common crimes and political offenses; that it
                    holds asylum should be granted only in case of political offense and that it
                    will decide accordingly each case that may be presented. Note is couched in
                    courteous terms and is accompanied by explanatory communiqué. Full text by
                        mail.<note n="18" xml:id="d479fn18">Copy of translation of the Foreign
                        Office communiqué published in <hi rend="italic">La Nación</hi>, September
                        1, 1943, transmitted to the Department by the Chargé in Argentina in his
                        despatch No. 11795, September 4.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
